Program: The History Hour
Title: Walking the Great Wall of China
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3csv0w8
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 1 Oct 2017
Walking the Great Wall of China; the death of Pope John Paul 1 after just a month in the job; turning against a colonial power - how Guinea gained independence from France; the life and times of anti-apartheid activist Steve Biko, and the British Land Girls of World War Two. (Picture: Yaohui Dong, Wu Deyu and Zhang Yuanhua on the Great Wall of China. Courtesy of Yaohui Dong) Show less